# Multi-User Concurrent Testing Scenario
# Tests multiple students taking the same exam simultaneously

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001/api
@adminToken = your-admin-token-here
@teacherToken = your-teacher-token-here
@student1Token = your-student1-token-here
@student2Token = your-student2-token-here
@student3Token = your-student3-token-here

### SETUP: Create exam for multi-user testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenDeThi": "Multi-User Test Exam",
  "moTa": "Exam for testing concurrent user access",
  "thoiGianLamBai": 45,
  "soLuongCauHoi": 5,
  "trangThai": true,
  "ngayBatDau": "2026-05-20T09:00:00",
  "ngayKetThuc": "2026-05-20T18:00:00",
  "cauHoiIds": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
}

### Store exam ID
@examId = {{$response.body.$.data.id}}

### CONCURRENT SCENARIO 1: Multiple students start exam at same time

### Student 1 starts exam
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Store session IDs
@session1Id = {{$response.body.$.data.sessionId}}

### Student 2 starts exam (concurrent)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{student2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

@session2Id = {{$response.body.$.data.sessionId}}

### Student 3 starts exam (concurrent)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{student3Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

@session3Id = {{$response.body.$.data.sessionId}}

### CONCURRENT SCENARIO 2: Students answer questions simultaneously

### Student 1 answers question 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 1,
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 30
}

### Student 2 answers question 1 (different answer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 1,
  "dapAnChon": "B",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 25
}

### Student 3 answers question 1 (different answer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student3Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 1,
  "dapAnChon": "C",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 35
}

### CONCURRENT SCENARIO 3: Mixed timing answers

### Student 1 answers question 2 quickly
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 2,
  "dapAnChon": "B",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 15
}

### Student 2 takes longer on question 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 2,
  "dapAnChon": "B",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 45
}

### Student 3 answers question 2 with medium time
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student3Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 2,
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 30
}

### CONCURRENT SCENARIO 4: Anti-cheat monitoring during concurrent access

### Student 1 - Normal behavior
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/anticheat
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loaiHanhVi": "FOCUS_LOST",
  "thoiGian": "2026-05-20T10:15:00",
  "chiTiet": "User switched to another tab briefly"
}

### Student 2 - Suspicious behavior
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/anticheat
Authorization: Bearer {{student2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loaiHanhVi": "COPY_PASTE",
  "thoiGian": "2026-05-20T10:16:00",
  "chiTiet": "Attempted to paste content"
}

### Student 3 - Multiple violations
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/anticheat
Authorization: Bearer {{student3Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loaiHanhVi": "TAB_SWITCH",
  "thoiGian": "2026-05-20T10:17:00",
  "chiTiet": "Switched tabs multiple times"
}

### CONCURRENT SCENARIO 5: Different submission times

### Student 1 submits early
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Student 2 continues and answers more questions
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 3,
  "dapAnChon": "C",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 40
}

### Student 3 also continues
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student3Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 3,
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 35
}

### Student 2 submits
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{student2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Student 3 submits last
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{student3Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### VERIFICATION: Check concurrent access results

### Teacher views all exam sessions
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Check individual results
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify anti-cheat logs for all sessions
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/anticheat-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/anticheat-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session3Id}}/anticheat-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Check exam statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/statistics
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### STRESS TEST: Rapid concurrent requests

### Multiple rapid answer submissions (simulate network lag/retry)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 4,
  "dapAnChon": "D",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 20
}

### Immediate second request (should handle gracefully)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 4,
  "dapAnChon": "D",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 20
}

### EDGE CASES: Concurrent edge scenarios

### Try to start exam that's already started
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Try to answer after submission
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session1Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{student1Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 5,
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 25
}

### CLEANUP
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### EXPECTED RESULTS:
# - All students should be able to start exam simultaneously
# - Each student should have unique session IDs
# - Answers should be isolated per student session
# - Anti-cheat logs should be tracked separately
# - No data corruption or race conditions
# - System should handle concurrent load gracefully
# - Edge cases should return appropriate error messages
# - Final results should be accurate for each student